The defendant David J West was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Defendant appeared in person, in custody, with Attorney Sebion.  State moves to amend charge to misdemeanor bail jumping.  Court granted.  Plead guilty to the amended charge.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  Defendant understood. Defense stipulates to a factual basis.   Court found that the defendant freely and voluntarily entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Joint recommendation for 18 months probation.  Defendant did not exercise his right to allocution.  Court ordered sentence withheld, 18 months probation.  Concurrent.    The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  May apply for expungement, if he succesfully completes probation.  No contact with females under the age of 18 years old, unless his agent expressly allows.  CC.  Submit DNA sample.  Seek and maintain employment/school as deemed appropriate by his agent.  Credit for 58 days served.
Plea/sentencing hearing at 06-22-2015 01:30 pm
Status conference at 07-13-2015 03:00 pm.
